{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781145176003,"sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","part":{"id":"prt_eb48687c1001cpQBdJVMp3ex7S","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"7636469d6e6ee8aa574de5560681d2e2704bc47d","messageID":"msg_eb48639df001735h4i0vHs4Nv2","sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":203595,"input":1516,"output":175,"reasoning":688,"cache":{"write":0,"read":201216}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781145177784,"sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","part":{"id":"prt_eb4868eb7001dqlF19dvCcn9Vp","messageID":"msg_eb48688a6001MUE3AeNvUxufuS","sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","snapshot":"7636469d6e6ee8aa574de5560681d2e2704bc47d","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781145187358,"sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9S1w7FwdJ4c0skQinjYAyIFr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":900},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Daemon CLI Reference\n3: description: Canonical reference for the three daemon-backed CLI shims over mk-spec-memory, mk-code-index, and mk-skill-advisor.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Daemon CLI Reference\n7: \n8: The daemon CLI shims are additive IPC clients over the existing MCP daemons. They are not replacement servers, and MCP remains the primary in-session transport.\n9: \n10: Use these CLIs when a runtime MCP transport is missing, failed, or not reconnecting while the daemon is expected to be warm, or when an operator needs shell diagnostics, CI checks, or scripted maintenance.\n11: \n12: ## 1. CLI Surfaces\n13: \n14: | CLI shim | MCP daemon | Tool count | Primary use |\n15: | --- | --- | ---: | --- |\n16: | `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` | `mk-spec-memory` | 37 | Memory context, search, health, indexing, checkpoint, and session recovery fallback. |\n17: | `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs` | `mk-code-index` | 8 | Code graph status, scan, verify, query, context, apply-mode recovery, and diff impact fallback. |\n18: | `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs` | `mk_skill_advisor` | 9 | Advisor recommendations, advisor health, skill graph diagnostics, and trusted maintainer mutations. |\n19: \n20: Each shim first checks its built CLI entrypoint, sets a default socket directory when needed, then runs the compiled CLI with inherited stdio. `list-tools` and `--help` are served from local definitions and do not contact or spawn a daemon.\n21: \n22: ## 2. Invocation Forms\n23: \n24: Common form:\n25: \n26: ```bash\n27: node .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs list-tools [--format json|text|jsonl]\n28: node .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs <tool_name> [--json '{...}'] [--format json|text|jsonl] [--timeout-ms N] [--warm-only]\n29: node .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs <tool_name> --param value [--another-param value]\n30: node .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs <tool_name> --help\n31: ```\n32: \n33: Tool names accept the aliases exposed by the CLI. The memory and code-index CLIs expose snake_case, kebab-case, and camelCase aliases from the tool name; the advisor CLI exposes aliases from its manifest.\n34: \n35: Use `--json` for one complete JSON object argument when a tool has structured input:\n36: \n37: ```bash\n38: node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_context --json '{\"input\":\"resume previous work\",\"mode\":\"resume\"}' --format json --timeout-ms 3000\n39: node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --format json --timeout-ms 3000 --warm-only\n40: node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_recommend --json '{\"prompt\":\"implement cli core\"}' --format json --timeout-ms 3000 --warm-only\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ## 3. Output Formats\n44: \n45: All three CLIs accept `--format json|text|jsonl`.\n46: \n47: | Format | Behavior |\n48: | --- | --- |\n49: | `json` | Pretty-printed JSON payload. |\n50: | `text` | Human-readable summary when the payload has one; `list-tools --format text` prints tool names. |\n51: | `jsonl` | A single complete JSON payload rendered on one stdout line. |\n52: \n53: `jsonl` is not streaming JSON Lines. Do not assume one record per tool, one record per result, or incremental output. When passing input with `--json`, pass one complete JSON object as one shell argument; the CLIs do not parse a stream of JSONL records from stdin.\n54: \n55: ## 4. Exit-Code Taxonomy\n56: \n57: | Exit | Meaning | Notes |\n58: | ---: | --- | --- |\n59: | `0` | Success | Includes actionable code-index `status:\"blocked\"` readiness refusals; blocked reads are valid answers with `requiredAction`. |\n60: | `1` | Runtime error | Tool returned an error payload or an unclassified runtime failure occurred. |\n61: | `64` | Usage or schema error | Bad flags, invalid `--json`, schema validation failure, advisor trusted-mutation refusal, or code-index `detect_changes` `parse_error`. |\n62: | `69` | Protocol mismatch or stale/missing dist | The shim or CLI refused an unsafe build/protocol state. Rebuild the matching package before retrying. |\n63: | `75` | Retryable daemon/IPC error | Warm-only daemon unavailable, connection refused/reset, timeout, busy database, spawn failure, or retryable backend state. |\n64: \n65: Exit `75` is retryable. Treat it as daemon or IPC unavailability, not as user input failure.\n66: \n67: ## 5. Warm-Only Policy\n68: \n69: Prompt-time hooks and prompt-time runtime fallbacks must use warm-only behavior. Warm-only probes the daemon socket and exits `75` when the daemon is cold instead of cold-spawning it.\n70: \n71: Use either the explicit flag or the prompt-time env flags:\n72: \n73: ```bash\n74: node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_stats --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000\n75: node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000\n76: node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000\n77: ```\n78: \n79: Warm-only defaults can also come from env flags documented in `../config/environment_variables.md` and `../../mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`: per-CLI `*_CLI_WARM_ONLY`, per-CLI `*_CLI_PROMPT_TIME`, cross-CLI `SPECKIT_CLI_PROMPT_TIME`, and runtime prompt-time markers such as `OPENCODE_PROMPT_TIME`, `CODEX_PROMPT_TIME`, and `CLAUDE_CODE_PROMPT_TIME`.\n80: \n81: Non-prompt contexts such as explicit operator maintenance, CI, cron, or session startup may omit `--warm-only`; then a cold daemon can auto-spawn through the matching `mk-*-launcher.cjs`.\n82: \n83: ## 6. Exit 69 Recovery\n84: \n85: The shims refuse stale or missing dist entrypoints with exit `69`. Rebuild before retrying.\n86: \n87: | CLI | Shim stale/missing message | Build recovery |\n88: | --- | --- | --- |\n89: | `spec-memory.cjs` | `Run npm run build --workspace=@spec-kit/mcp-server.` | `npm run build --workspace=@spec-kit/mcp-server` |\n90: | `code-index.cjs` | `Run tsc -p .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/tsconfig.json.` | `npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-code-graph run build` or the exact `tsc -p ...` command from the shim. |\n91: | `skill-advisor.cjs` | `Run the skill-advisor TypeScript build.` | `npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run build` |\n92: \n93: Development-only stale overrides exist for local loops, but should not be used in normal recovery: `SPECKIT_SPEC_MEMORY_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1`, `SPECKIT_CODE_INDEX_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1`, and `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1` or `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1`.\n94: \n95: ## 7. Help And Discovery\n96: \n97: Use `list-tools` for offline surface discovery:\n98: \n99: ```bash\n100: node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs list-tools --format json\n101: node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs list-tools --format json\n102: node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs list-tools --format json\n103: ```\n104: \n105: Expected counts are `37`, `8`, and `9` respectively.\n106: \n107: Per-command help is available and prints the command description, aliases, and input schema:\n108: \n109: ```bash\n110: node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_stats --help\n111: node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --help\n112: node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --help\n113: ```\n114: \n115: Run the host-safe offline smoke check to verify all three shims without daemon contact:\n116: \n117: ```bash\n118: node .opencode/bin/cli-offline-smoke.cjs --format json\n119: ```\n120: \n121: The smoke check expects `spec-memory=37`, `code-index=8`, `skill-advisor=9`, and `daemonFree:true` for each result.\n122: \n123: ## 8. Safety Rules\n124: \n125: - Keep MCP as the primary in-session transport; use CLIs as additive fallbacks and operator surfaces.\n126: - Prefer read-only recovery commands when transport fails: memory context/status, code graph status/query reads, advisor recommend/status.\n127: - Prompt-time hooks must probe warm daemons only. They must not cold-spawn daemons from prompt-time paths.\n128: - Treat exit `75` as retryable daemon/IPC unavailability. Retry after MCP reconnect, daemon prewarm, or short backoff.\n129: - Treat exit `69` as a stale/missing dist or protocol mismatch. Rebuild the matching package before retrying.\n130: - Keep code-index maintenance commands such as `code_graph_scan`, `code_graph_apply`, and `code_graph_verify` out of prompt-time hooks.\n131: - Skill-advisor CLI calls are untrusted by default. Mutations (`advisor_rebuild`, `skill_graph_scan`, and apply-mode `skill_graph_propagate_enhances`) require `--trusted` or `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_TRUSTED=1`.\n132: - Do not use `jsonl` as a streaming automation contract; it is one complete JSON payload on one line.\n133: \n134: ## 9. Source Anchors\n135: \n136: - CLI sources: `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, `system-code-graph/mcp_server/code-index-cli.ts`, `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/skill-advisor-cli.ts`.\n137: - Shim sources: `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/code-index.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs`.\n138: - Env flags: `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md` section `CLI FRONT DOOR (DUAL-STACK)`.\n139: - Offline smoke: `.opencode/bin/cli-offline-smoke.cjs`.\n\n(End of file - total 139 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Daemon CLI Reference\ndescription: Canonical reference for the three daemon-backed CLI shims over mk-spec-memory, mk-code-index, and mk-skill-advisor.\n---\n\n# Daemon CLI Reference\n\nThe daemon CLI shims are additive IPC clients over the existing MCP daemons. They are not replacement servers, and MCP remains the primary in-session transport.\n\nUse these CLIs when a runtime MCP transport is missing, failed, or not reconnecting while the daemon is expected to be warm, or when an operator needs shell diagnostics, CI checks, or scripted maintenance.\n\n## 1. CLI Surfaces\n\n| CLI shim | MCP daemon | Tool count | Primary use |\n| --- | --- | ---: | --- |\n| `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` | `mk-spec-memory` | 37 | Memory context, search, health, indexing, checkpoint, and session recovery fallback. |\n| `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs` | `mk-code-index` | 8 | Code graph status, scan, verify, query, context, apply-mode recovery, and diff impact fallback. |\n| `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs` | `mk_skill_advisor` | 9 | Advisor recommendations, advisor health, skill graph diagnostics, and trusted maintainer mutations. |\n\nEach shim first checks its built CLI entrypoint, sets a default socket directory when needed, then runs the compiled CLI with inherited stdio. `list-tools` and `--help` are served from local definitions and do not contact or spawn a daemon.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Daemon CLI Reference\ndescription: Canonical reference for the three daemon-backed CLI shims over mk-spec-memory, mk-code-index, and mk-skill-advisor.\n---\n\n# Daemon CLI Reference\n\nThe daemon CLI shims are additive IPC clients over the existing MCP daemons. They are not replacement servers, and MCP remains the primary in-session transport.\n\nUse these CLIs when a runtime MCP transport is missing, failed, or not reconnecting while the daemon is expected to be warm, or when an operator needs shell diagnostics, CI checks, or scripted maintenance.\n\n## 1. CLI Surfaces\n\n| CLI shim | MCP daemon | Tool count | Primary use |\n| --- | --- | ---: | --- |\n| `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` | `mk-spec-memory` | 37 | Memory context, search, health, indexing, checkpoint, and session recovery fallback. |\n| `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs` | `mk-code-index` | 8 | Code graph status, scan, verify, query, context, apply-mode recovery, and diff impact fallback. |\n| `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs` | `mk_skill_advisor` | 9 | Advisor recommendations, advisor health, skill graph diagnostics, and trusted maintainer mutations. |\n\nEach shim first checks its built CLI entrypoint, sets a default socket directory when needed, then runs the compiled CLI with inherited stdio. `list-tools` and `--help` are served from local definitions and do not contact or spawn a daemon.\n\n## 2. Invocation Forms\n\nCommon form:\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs list-tools [--format json|text|jsonl]\nnode .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs <tool_name> [--json '{...}'] [--format json|text|jsonl] [--timeout-ms N] [--warm-only]\nnode .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs <tool_name> --param value [--another-param value]\nnode .opencode/bin/<cli>.cjs <tool_name> --help\n```\n\nTool names accept the aliases exposed by the CLI. The memory and code-index CLIs expose snake_case, kebab-case, and camelCase aliases from the tool name; the advisor CLI exposes aliases from its manifest.\n\nUse `--json` for one complete JSON object argument when a tool has structured input:\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_context --json '{\"input\":\"resume previous work\",\"mode\":\"resume\"}' --format json --timeout-ms 3000\nnode .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --format json --timeout-ms 3000 --warm-only\nnode .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_recommend --json '{\"prompt\":\"implement cli core\"}' --format json --timeout-ms 3000 --warm-only\n```\n\n## 3. Output Formats\n\nAll three CLIs accept `--format json|text|jsonl`.\n\n| Format | Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| `json` | Pretty-printed JSON payload. |\n| `text` | Human-readable summary when the payload has one; `list-tools --format text` prints tool names. |\n| `jsonl` | A single complete JSON payload rendered on one stdout line. |\n\n`jsonl` is not streaming JSON Lines. Do not assume one record per tool, one record per result, or incremental output. When passing input with `--json`, pass one complete JSON object as one shell argument; the CLIs do not parse a stream of JSONL records from stdin.\n\n## 4. Exit-Code Taxonomy\n\n| Exit | Meaning | Notes |\n| ---: | --- | --- |\n| `0` | Success | Includes actionable code-index `status:\"blocked\"` readiness refusals; blocked reads are valid answers with `requiredAction`. |\n| `1` | Runtime error | Tool returned an error payload or an unclassified runtime failure occurred. |\n| `64` | Usage or schema error | Bad flags, invalid `--json`, schema validation failure, advisor trusted-mutation refusal, or code-index `detect_changes` `parse_error`. |\n| `69` | Protocol mismatch or stale/missing dist | The shim or CLI refused an unsafe build/protocol state. Rebuild the matching package before retrying. |\n| `75` | Retryable daemon/IPC error | Warm-only daemon unavailable, connection refused/reset, timeout, busy database, spawn failure, or retryable backend state. |\n\nExit `75` is retryable. Treat it as daemon or IPC unavailability, not as user input failure.\n\n## 5. Warm-Only Policy\n\nPrompt-time hooks and prompt-time runtime fallbacks must use warm-only behavior. Warm-only probes the daemon socket and exits `75` when the daemon is cold instead of cold-spawning it.\n\nUse either the explicit flag or the prompt-time env flags:\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_stats --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000\nnode .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000\nnode .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000\n```\n\nWarm-only defaults can also come from env flags documented in `../config/environment_variables.md` and `../../mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`: per-CLI `*_CLI_WARM_ONLY`, per-CLI `*_CLI_PROMPT_TIME`, cross-CLI `SPECKIT_CLI_PROMPT_TIME`, and runtime prompt-time markers such as `OPENCODE_PROMPT_TIME`, `CODEX_PROMPT_TIME`, and `CLAUDE_CODE_PROMPT_TIME`.\n\nNon-prompt contexts such as explicit operator maintenance, CI, cron, or session startup may omit `--warm-only`; then a cold daemon can auto-spawn through the matching `mk-*-launcher.cjs`.\n\n## 6. Exit 69 Recovery\n\nThe shims refuse stale or missing dist entrypoints with exit `69`. Rebuild before retrying.\n\n| CLI | Shim stale/missing message | Build recovery |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `spec-memory.cjs` | `Run npm run build --workspace=@spec-kit/mcp-server.` | `npm run build --workspace=@spec-kit/mcp-server` |\n| `code-index.cjs` | `Run tsc -p .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/tsconfig.json.` | `npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-code-graph run build` or the exact `tsc -p ...` command from the shim. |\n| `skill-advisor.cjs` | `Run the skill-advisor TypeScript build.` | `npm --prefix .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server run build` |\n\nDevelopment-only stale overrides exist for local loops, but should not be used in normal recovery: `SPECKIT_SPEC_MEMORY_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1`, `SPECKIT_CODE_INDEX_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1`, and `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1` or `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_DEV_ALLOW_STALE=1`.\n\n## 7. Help And Discovery\n\nUse `list-tools` for offline surface discovery:\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs list-tools --format json\nnode .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs list-tools --format json\nnode .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs list-tools --format json\n```\n\nExpected counts are `37`, `8`, and `9` respectively.\n\nPer-command help is available and prints the command description, aliases, and input schema:\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_stats --help\nnode .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --help\nnode .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --help\n```\n\nRun the host-safe offline smoke check to verify all three shims without daemon contact:\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/bin/cli-offline-smoke.cjs --format json\n```\n\nThe smoke check expects `spec-memory=37`, `code-index=8`, `skill-advisor=9`, and `daemonFree:true` for each result.\n\n## 8. Safety Rules\n\n- Keep MCP as the primary in-session transport; use CLIs as additive fallbacks and operator surfaces.\n- Prefer read-only recovery commands when transport fails: memory context/status, code graph status/query reads, advisor recommend/status.\n- Prompt-time hooks must probe warm daemons only. They must not cold-spawn daemons from prompt-time paths.\n- Treat exit `75` as retryable daemon/IPC unavailability. Retry after MCP reconnect, daemon prewarm, or short backoff.\n- Treat exit `69` as a stale/missing dist or protocol mismatch. Rebuild the matching package before retrying.\n- Keep code-index maintenance commands such as `code_graph_scan`, `code_graph_apply`, and `code_graph_verify` out of prompt-time hooks.\n- Skill-advisor CLI calls are untrusted by default. Mutations (`advisor_rebuild`, `skill_graph_scan`, and apply-mode `skill_graph_propagate_enhances`) require `--trusted` or `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_TRUSTED=1`.\n- Do not use `jsonl` as a streaming automation contract; it is one complete JSON payload on one line.\n\n## 9. Source Anchors\n\n- CLI sources: `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, `system-code-graph/mcp_server/code-index-cli.ts`, `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/skill-advisor-cli.ts`.\n- Shim sources: `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/code-index.cjs`, `.opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs`.\n- Env flags: `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md` section `CLI FRONT DOOR (DUAL-STACK)`.\n- Offline smoke: `.opencode/bin/cli-offline-smoke.cjs`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":139,"totalLines":139,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md","time":{"start":1781145187349,"end":1781145187356}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c8f2e73f164b31016a2a1e633fb88191b60de1d7bb28611a"}},"id":"prt_eb486b3d8001CvyM5W3637fHs7","sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","messageID":"msg_eb48688a6001MUE3AeNvUxufuS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781145187383,"sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_IyKqS3us38eGV39wO8pnfkn0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"Daemon CLI Reference|jsonl|exit.*69|spec-memory.cjs|code-index.cjs|skill-advisor.cjs","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/SKILL.md","include":"SKILL.md"},"output":"Found 2 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/SKILL.md:\n  Line 286: The surface is dual-stack: every tool above is also callable through the daemon-backed CLI `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool_name> [--json '{...}' | --param value]` against the same daemon (MCP registration unchanged). Recovery example: `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --format json --timeout-ms 3000 --warm-only`. Flag values are coerced against the tool's input schema. Exit taxonomy: `0` success, `1` runtime, `64` usage/schema (including `detect_changes` `parse_error` on a malformed diff), `69` protocol/dist mismatch or stale dist, `75` retryable daemon error. Blocked-read rendering is preserved: a `status:\"blocked\"` readiness refusal exits `0` with the `requiredAction` surfaced — an actionable answer, not a failure. Prompt-time callers must pass `--warm-only` (probe-only; exit `75` on a cold daemon); other contexts auto-spawn via `mk-code-index-launcher.cjs`. `--format jsonl` renders one complete JSON payload on one stdout line; it is not streaming JSON Lines. Full cross-daemon CLI behavior, recovery, stale-dist build commands, per-command `--help`, offline smoke, and safety rules live in [`../system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md).\n\n  Line 369: | CLI callers (hooks, scripts, CI, transport-down recovery) | Daemon-backed `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool>` over the same daemon. The Claude/Codex hook adapters fall back through `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/code-index-cli-fallback.ts` (warm-only), and the OpenCode plugin bridge (`mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-code-graph-bridge.mjs`) routes through the CLI with `SPECKIT_CODE_INDEX_CLI_PROMPT_TIME=1`. |\n","metadata":{"matches":2,"truncated":false},"title":"Daemon CLI Reference|jsonl|exit.*69|spec-memory.cjs|code-index.cjs|skill-advisor.cjs","time":{"start":1781145187367,"end":1781145187376}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c8f2e73f164b31016a2a1e633fc881918eb13135438d75bc"}},"id":"prt_eb486b417001Ij10N0Pib62RfB","sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","messageID":"msg_eb48688a6001MUE3AeNvUxufuS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781145187430,"sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_5oSs5GeTTT6Bs88XAeyQPE4L","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"Daemon CLI Reference|jsonl|exit.*69|spec-memory.cjs|code-index.cjs|skill-advisor.cjs","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md","include":"SKILL.md"},"output":"Found 5 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:\n  Line 261: - **Advisor MCP unavailable:** for normal Gate 2 routing, fall back to Python `skill_advisor.py` only when the caller needs the legacy JSON-array facade or MCP/CLI transport is unavailable. Use `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms N` for operator checks, doctor routes and runtime fallbacks that have already verified a warm `mk-skill-advisor` daemon socket. Prompt-time hooks must probe the socket first, never cold-spawn the daemon, and fail open on CLI exit 75 before keyword matching against frontmatter `trigger_phrases`. Full cross-daemon CLI behavior, recovery, exit taxonomy, stale-dist build commands, per-command `--help`, offline smoke, and `jsonl` semantics live in [`../system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md).\n\n  Line 267: - Use `.opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs` for daemon-backed CLI checks and runtime fallback only after a warm-socket probe succeeds; always pass `--timeout-ms` and treat exit 75 as retryable fail-open.\n\n  Line 303: The surface is dual-stack: the same nine tools are callable through the daemon-backed CLI `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool_name>` over the same daemon (the MCP registration is unchanged). Recovery example: `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_recommend --json '{\"prompt\":\"<request>\"}' --warm-only --format json --timeout-ms 3000`. CLI exit taxonomy: `0` success, `1` runtime, `64` usage/schema or trusted-mutation refusal, `69` protocol/dist mismatch or stale dist, `75` retryable daemon error. `--format jsonl` renders one complete JSON payload on one stdout line; it is not streaming JSON Lines. Trust resolution fails closed: the daemon treats a caller as untrusted when transport `_meta` is absent or unknown, the CLI sends `callerAuthority: untrusted` unless `--trusted`/`MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_CLI_TRUSTED=1` is supplied, and native MCP surfaces whose clients send no `_meta` are re-granted default trust only through `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT=trusted` in the daemon's own environment (set in the committed MCP registrations: `.mcp.json`, `opencode.json`, `.codex/config.toml`), which callers cannot forge. An env-gated tri-daemon drill (`SPECKIT_RUN_TRI_DAEMON_DRILL=1`, `mcp_server/tests/tri-daemon-drill.vitest.ts`) exercises all three daemon-backed CLIs together.\n\n  Line 388: - Prompt-time hooks for Claude, Codex and OpenCode. The Claude/Codex hooks share the warm-only CLI fallback helper `hooks/lib/skill-advisor-cli-fallback.ts`; the OpenCode plugin bridge (`mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`) falls back to `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs --warm-only` when its bridge path is unavailable.\n\n  Line 390: - Daemon-backed CLI callers (`node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool>`) for doctor routes, scripts and CI — untrusted by default, `--trusted` for maintainer mutations.\n","metadata":{"matches":5,"truncated":false},"title":"Daemon CLI Reference|jsonl|exit.*69|spec-memory.cjs|code-index.cjs|skill-advisor.cjs","time":{"start":1781145187418,"end":1781145187430}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c8f2e73f164b31016a2a1e633fd0819193e40afd600d4a5b"}},"id":"prt_eb486b42a001UAuklw8WXkKhXM","sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","messageID":"msg_eb48688a6001MUE3AeNvUxufuS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781145187529,"sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_GRPP2u3iyXjVbObQrb9OTqpr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"Daemon CLI Reference|jsonl|exit.*69|spec-memory.cjs|code-index.cjs|skill-advisor.cjs","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md","include":"SKILL.md"},"output":"Found 2 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:\n  Line 413: The surface is dual-stack: alongside the `mk-spec-memory` MCP registration, all 37 tools are callable through the daemon-backed CLI `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool_name> [--json '{...}' | --param value]` against the same daemon. Recovery example: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_context --json '{\"input\":\"resume previous work\",\"mode\":\"resume\"}' --format json --timeout-ms 3000`. CLI exit taxonomy: `0` success, `1` runtime, `64` usage/schema, `69` protocol/dist mismatch or stale dist, `75` retryable daemon error. Prompt-time callers must pass `--warm-only` (probe-only, exit `75` instead of cold-spawning); non-prompt contexts auto-spawn the daemon through the launcher. `--format jsonl` renders one complete JSON payload on one stdout line; it is not streaming JSON Lines. Full cross-daemon CLI behavior, recovery, stale-dist build commands, per-command `--help`, offline smoke, and safety rules live in [`references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md`](references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md). See `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md` (\"CLI front door\") for the warm-only/prompt-time env flags. Detailed behavior, flags, scoring, and MCP tool reference live in `references/memory/memory_system.md`, `references/memory/save_workflow.md`, and `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`. Launcher/daemon reliability is operator-tunable via the `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG`, `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES`, `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP`, and `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` (default-on in the runtime configs: a disposing owner releases the shared daemon for a live secondary, and a fresh session reaps the released daemon before respawn for a single writer) flags, all documented in `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`.\n\n  Line 512: | Memory CLI (dual-stack) | `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --format json` calls any of the 37 memory tools over the live daemon; `list-tools` enumerates them offline; `--warm-only` for prompt-time contexts |\n","metadata":{"matches":2,"truncated":false},"title":"Daemon CLI Reference|jsonl|exit.*69|spec-memory.cjs|code-index.cjs|skill-advisor.cjs","time":{"start":1781145187518,"end":1781145187528}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c8f2e73f164b31016a2a1e633fd88191bc48cec252b78f11"}},"id":"prt_eb486b461001QYDDLceO7fua4V","sessionID":"ses_14b7dcdd9ffeTUJ25ZqyT2Zeky","messageID":"msg_eb48688a6001MUE3AeNvUxufuS"}}
